# attestor-unit-build-ledger.psv
# ZKNOT Attestor seed-r1 — unit-build + label-print tracking ledger (SOP-ATTESTOR-001 §8)
# LIVING, APPEND-ONLY. Do not rewrite rows; append corrections as new rows w/ note. GPG-sign commits.
# Identity source of truth: ~/ZKNOT/P-ZKKEY/atecc-provisioning-ledger.psv (serial <-> pubkey)
#
# WORKFLOW (per unit, handoff §6):
#   1. Read serial from board boot banner / verify_unit.py
#   2. Confirm serial enrolled in provisioning ledger  -> enrolled=Y (NEVER label an unenrolled chip)
#   3. Functional check: unit signs against its enrolled key -> verify_tested=Y
#   4. Print label for THAT serial (no batch-printing detached from boards)
#   5. Pot -> potted=Y ; record sale ref when sold
#
# FIXED LABEL CONTENT (every seed-r1 commercial unit — do NOT vary):
#   ZKNOT ATTESTOR / seed-r1 / PRESENCE-TIER · SELF-ASSERTED / Verify verifyknot.io / ZKNOT, INC.
#   NO CAGE (commercial). NO "secure element" / tamper / FIPS / assurance verbs.
#   QR target: verifyknot.io/v/<serial-lowercase> IF route live (curl check), else verifyknot.io/start
#   Serial printed grouped 4-4-4-4-2 human-readable; QR encodes ungrouped lowercase.
#
# Columns:
# build_no | serial_raw(lowercase,18hex) | serial_grouped | enrolled | verify_tested | label_printed | qr_target | potted | build_date | operator | sale_ref | notes
